        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Question: A mild shaft of 50mm diameter is subject a BM of 2000 Nm and torque (T). Permissible yield of material is 200 MPa. Find the maximum value of the torque that can be applied on the shaft by using maximum - 1) maxy strain theory, assume poission ration is 0.3."
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 1,
          "text": "Solution:"
        },
        {
          "type": "math",
          "latex": "d = 50 mm",
          "display": true
        },
        {
          "type": "math",
          "latex": "BM = 2000 Nm = 2000 \\times 10^3 Nmm = 2 \\times 10^6 Nmm",
          "display": true
        },
        {
          "type": "math",
          "latex": "(\\sigma_y)_{Permissible} = 200 \\times 10^6 N/m^2 = 200 \\times 10^6 N / 10^6 mm^2 = 200 N/mm^2",
          "display": true
        },
        {
          "type": "math",
          "latex": "D = 0.3",
          "display": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}